[I] Simple terminal UI for git commands

[T] Lazygit is a lightweight, terminal-base git user interface designed to
[T] simplify repository management. It provides an intuitive and visually
[T] organized way to handle git operations, such as commits, branches and
[T] merges.

[U] https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit

[A] Lazygit Authors
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/base

[E] add git

[V] 0.63.1
[L] MIT

[D] 7a153d42b5dfd2a9df829b12aff15b8f46e90d78f5d1353ec5bc5a1c lazygit-0.63.1.tar.gz https://github.com/jesseduffield/lazygit/archive/v0.63.1/

runjust=0

hook_add postmake 5 'install -m755 lazygit $root$bindir/'
